            "description": "Implement periodic transaction payee feature",
            "prompt": "You need to implement a feature for the Ledger accounting software (C++ codebase at /Users/johnw/src/ledger/fix-2044).\n\n## Feature: Allow periodic transactions to have an optional payee (GitHub issue #2044)\n\nCurrently, periodic transactions look like:\n```\n~ monthly\n    Expenses:Food    $500\n    Assets:Checking\n```\n\nThe feature request is to allow periodic transactions to specify an optional payee, like:\n```\n~ monthly  Grocery Store\n    Expenses:Food    $500\n    Assets:Checking\n```\n\nWhen a payee is specified, the synthetic budget/forecast transactions generated from this periodic entry should use that payee instead of the default \"Budget transaction\" / \"Forecast transaction\".\n\n## Current Implementation\n\n**`src/xact.h` line ~400**: `period_xact_t` has `period` and `period_string` fields but no `payee` field.\n\n**`src/textual_xacts.cc` line 303**: \n```cpp\nunique_ptr<period_xact_t> pe(new period_xact_t(skip_ws(line + 1)));\n```\nThis passes the entire rest of the header line to `date_interval_t`, which fails if it encounters non-period tokens.\n\n**`src/filters.cc` line 1635-1642** (`generate_posts::add_period_xacts`):\n```cpp\nvoid generate_posts::add_period_xacts(period_xacts_list& period_xacts) {\n  for (period_xact_t* xact : period_xacts)\n    for (post_t* post : xact->posts)\n      if (!post->has_flags(ITEM_GENERATED) || post->has_flags(POST_CALCULATED))\n        add_post(xact->period, *post);\n}\n```\n\n**`src/filters.cc` line 1714**: `xact.payee = _(\"Budget transaction\");`\n**`src/filters.cc` line 1886**: `xact.payee = _(\"Forecast transaction\");`\n\n**`src/post.cc` line 202-208** (payee() method):\n```cpp\nstring post_t::payee() const {\n  if (_payee)\n    return *_payee;\n  string post_payee = payee_from_tag();\n  return post_payee != \"\" ? post_payee : xact ? xact->payee : \"\";\n}\n```\nFor period posts, `xact` is null, so returns \"\" if no `_payee` or Payee tag.\n\n## Implementation Plan\n\n### 1. `src/xact.h`: Add `payee` field to `period_xact_t`\n\nAdd `string payee;` field and update the copy constructor.\n\n### 2. `src/textual_xacts.cc`: Parse payee from header line\n\nIn `period_xact_directive()`, split the header line (the part after `~ `) on the first double-space or tab. The left part is the period expression; the right part (trimmed) is the payee.\n\nThe parsing logic:\n- Scan `header` char by char\n- If we find `\\t` → that's the separator: period is everything before, payee is everything after (trimmed)\n- If we find 2+ consecutive spaces → that's the separator: period is everything before first space in the run, payee is everything after the whitespace run (trimmed)  \n- Handle trailing `; note` in the payee part too (strip it off)\n- If no separator found → no payee\n\nAfter extracting period_str and payee_str:\n```cpp\nunique_ptr<period_xact_t> pe(new period_xact_t(period_str));\nif (!payee_str.empty())\n    pe->payee = context.journal->validate_payee(payee_str);\n```\n\n### 3. `src/filters.cc`: Propagate payee from period_xact to posts\n\nIn `generate_posts::add_period_xacts()`, after the existing check, set the post's payee:\n```cpp\nif (!xact->payee.empty() && post->payee().empty())\n    post->set_payee(xact->payee);\n```\n\nThen in `budget_posts::report_budget_items()`:\n```cpp\nstring post_payee = post.payee();\nxact.payee = post_payee.empty() ? _(\"Budget transaction\") : post_payee;\n```\n\nAnd in `forecast_posts::operator()`:\n```cpp\nstring post_payee = post.payee();\nxact.payee = post_payee.empty() ? _(\"Forecast transaction\") : post_payee;\n```\n\n## Please implement the following changes:\n\n1. Read the relevant sections of the files first\n2. Make the minimal changes needed\n3. Don't add unnecessary documentation, comments, or refactoring\n\nFiles to modify:\n- `/Users/johnw/src/ledger/fix-2044/src/xact.h` (add payee field to period_xact_t)\n- `/Users/johnw/src/ledger/fix-2044/src/textual_xacts.cc` (parse payee from header line)\n- `/Users/johnw/src/ledger/fix-2044/src/filters.cc` (use payee in budget/forecast generation)\n\nKey considerations:\n- The payee separator on the periodic header line is: tab OR two or more consecutive spaces\n- If the payee part contains ` ; note`, strip the note portion (the note should still be handled as a note)\n- Validate the payee through `context.journal->validate_payee()`\n- For budget: use the payee if set, else fall back to \"Budget transaction\"\n- For forecast: use the payee if set, else fall back to \"Forecast transaction\"\n- Also handle notes after the payee: if there's a `; note` after the payee in the header, the note should be appended to the period_xact similar to how regular transactions handle notes\n\nAfter making changes, also write a regression test at `/Users/johnw/src/ledger/fix-2044/test/regress/2044.test` that:\n1. Tests that budget transactions use the period payee\n2. Tests that forecast transactions use the period payee\n\nLook at existing test files like `/Users/johnw/src/ledger/fix-2044/test/regress/coverage-budget-report.test` and `/Users/johnw/src/ledger/fix-2044/test/regress/370-forecast_period_weeks.test` for the test format.\n\nDo NOT run builds - just make the code changes and write the test file.",
